# Updating the Remote Repo (git push)

When the user asks to **push to the remote**, **update the remote repo**, or **sync to GitHub**:

1. Run `git add`, `git commit`, and `git push` as appropriate.
2. For **`git push`** (and any `git push origin â€¦`), request **network** permission so the push can reach the remote. Use `required_permissions: ["network"]` (or `["network","all"]` if SSH/credentials need full access) when running the push command.

The user has confirmed Git auth (HTTPS credential helper or SSH) works from a normal terminal; the main requirement is that the agent run `git push` with network allowed.
